abstract: Democratic presidential candidates seeking victory in next week's Iowa caucuses are navigating a field that is so jumbled that voters' second choice could matter almost as much as their first, adding fresh uncertainty and confusion to the final days of the race.
snippet: Democratic presidential candidates seeking victory in next week's Iowa caucuses are navigating a field that is so jumbled that voters' second choice could matter almost as much as their first, adding fresh uncertainty and confusion to the final da...
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES, Iowa — Democratic presidential candidates seeking victory in next week's Iowa caucuses are navigating a field that is so jumbled that voters' second choice could matter almost as much as their first, adding fresh uncertainty and confusion to the final days of the race.
headline_main: Voters' 2nd Choices Could Be Decisive in Close Iowa Caucuses
headline_print_headline: Voters' 2nd Choices Could Be Decisive in Close Iowa Caucuses

abstract: A Coast Guard lieutenant accused by prosecutors of being a domestic terrorist intent on committing politically motivated killings inspired by a far-right mass murderer was sentenced Friday to more than 13 years in prison for firearms and drug offenses.
snippet: A Coast Guard lieutenant accused by prosecutors of being a domestic terrorist intent on committing politically motivated killings inspired by a far-right mass murderer was sentenced Friday to more than 13 years in prison for firearms and drug offe...
lead_paragraph: GREENBELT, Md. — A Coast Guard lieutenant accused by prosecutors of being a domestic terrorist intent on committing politically motivated killings inspired by a far-right mass murderer was sentenced Friday to more than 13 years in prison for firearms and drug offenses.
headline_main: Coast Guard Officer-Terror Suspect Sentenced for Guns, Drugs
headline_print_headline: Coast Guard Officer-Terror Suspect Sentenced for Guns, Drugs

abstract: Senator Lamar Alexander said he would not vote for new witnesses — a possible death blow to the Democrats’ case.

abstract: Andrew Yang is showing what healthy populism looks like.
snippet: Andrew Yang is showing what healthy populism looks like.
lead_paragraph: It was New Year’s Eve, and I had decided to spend it with Andrew Yang. A self-described “Asian man who’s good at math,” Mr. Yang had raised an impressive $16.5 million in the fourth quarter of 2019 for his presidential campaign. Despite being newly flush, the campaign didn’t hold its shindig in a Napa Valley wine cave or at Gramercy Tavern, but in a fluorescent-lit room above a bar in Nashua, N.H.

abstract: Four Democratic presidential candidates hoping for success in the state remained in Washington for President Trump’s Senate trial.
snippet: Four Democratic presidential candidates hoping for success in the state remained in Washington for President Trump’s Senate trial.
lead_paragraph: DES MOINES — Four Democratic presidential candidates hoping for breakout performances in the Iowa caucuses next week spent Thursday in Washington listening to questioning in the Senate impeachment trial of President Trump.

abstract: Democratic presidential candidates seeking victory in next week's Iowa caucuses are navigating a field that is so jumbled that voters' second choice could matter almost as much as their first, adding fresh uncertainty and confusion to the final days of the race.

lead_paragraph: DES MOINES, Iowa — Democratic presidential candidates seeking victory in next week's Iowa caucuses are navigating a field that is so jumbled that voters' second choice could matter almost as much as their first, adding fresh uncertainty and confusion to the final days of the race.
headline_main: Voters' 2nd Choices Could Be Decisive in Close Iowa Caucuses

abstract: Pete Buttigieg and Joe Biden stepped up their criticisms of Bernie Sanders on Thursday, as moderates are under growing pressure to dull any momentum the progressive senator may gain heading into next week's Iowa caucuses.

lead_paragraph: WAUKEE, Iowa — Pete Buttigieg and Joe Biden stepped up their criticisms of Bernie Sanders on Thursday, as moderates are under growing pressure to dull any momentum the progressive senator may gain heading into next week's Iowa caucuses.
